div.p: MS 58 (044) MUE, Herbarium of Western Australia, Perth.

Most likely in 1890s.
Why, need a dating justification

the number 2 is at the top of the list in the same hand that wrote 3 in the middle of the previous letter.
This is consistent with someone numbering lists, but does not mean that the list was preceded by anything. See also comments below under fn 8

note.p: Tysoni added in another hand. The name P. tysoni was not published until 1931, in C. Gardner (1930-1), part 3, p. 114, where it was attributed to 'F.v.M' but without a description. The name is given on a Gardner label for a specimen (PERTH 01292994) collected by Tyson in 1898.
